a-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-22_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-24_">What is induction training?</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_induction_training-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690546699" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_induction_training-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690546699 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_induction_training-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690546699 320w" width="2453" height="1637" alt="What is induction training- The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="What is induction training- The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:2453 / 1637" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-25_"/><p class="sc-ljMRFG jiRhOP pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-28_">Induction training holds immense significance in the UK health and social care sector as it is the foundational pillar for ensuring the safety, well-being, and quality of care provided to vulnerable individuals.<br><br>The <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/products/care-certificate-train-the-trainer-trainer-pack-cpduk-accredited?variant=31839814582341" target="_blank"><i>Care Certificate</i></a> is regarded as the standard for induction training. It is specifically created for the non-regulated workforce and ensures that all health and care professionals possess the necessary introductory skills, knowledge, and behaviours to provide compassionate, safe, and high-quality care and support in their workplace setting.<br><br>By acquainting new employees with the specific risks, hazards, and safe practices within the environment, induction training empowers them to identify and mitigate potential dangers, thus reducing the likelihood of workplace incidents and accidents.<br><br>Compliance with legal requirements, as mandated by the Health and Safety at Work etc. Act 1974 is effectively achieved through comprehensive induction training, guaranteeing that employees are adequately informed and trained to prioritise health and safety in their daily tasks. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-31_">Reasons for induction training</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Reasons_for_induction_training-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_e5c67721-cc5a-4c73-8aa1-961fe970c6dc.jpg?v=1690547476" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Reasons_for_induction_training-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_e5c67721-cc5a-4c73-8aa1-961fe970c6dc.jpg?v=1690547476 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Reasons_for_induction_training-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_e5c67721-cc5a-4c73-8aa1-961fe970c6dc_500x.jpg?v=1690547476 320w" width="1050" height="627" alt="Reasons for induction training- The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Reasons for induction training- The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:1050 / 627" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-32_"/><p class="sc-ljMRFG jiRhOP pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-35_">Induction training is essential to any company's training and development strategy, providing new employees with the necessary knowledge, skills, and tools to hit the ground running and contribute to the organisation's success.<br><br>The importance of induction training cannot be overstated, as it sets the tone for new employees and can significantly impact their productivity, job satisfaction, and long-term success within the organisation. We have outlined some reasons why an induction training programme is needed.</span></p><h4 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-36_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-38_">Introduction to workplace risks</span></h4><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Introduction_to_workplace_risks-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690548134" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Introduction_to_workplace_risks-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690548134 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Introduction_to_workplace_risks-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690548134 320w" width="2800" height="1867" alt="Introduction to workplace risks- The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Introduction to workplace risks- The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:2800 / 1867" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-39_"/><p class="sc-ljMRFG jiRhOP pf-40_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-42_">The Management of Health and Safety at Work Regulations 1999 require employers to protect their employees and others from harm. Training new employees to understand the hazards and risks involved in health and social care reduces the likelihood of accidents and incidents by making them aware of potential hazards and how to deal with them.</span></p><h4 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-43_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-45_">Compliance with legal requirements</span></h4><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Induction_training_-_Compliance_with_legal_requirements_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690548838" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Induction_training_-_Compliance_with_legal_requirements_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690548838 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Induction_training_-_Compliance_with_legal_requirements_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690548838 320w" width="2000" height="1311" alt="Induction training - Compliance with legal requirements - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Induction training - Compliance with legal requirements - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:2000 / 1311" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-46_"/><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-47_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The HSE requires employers to provide adequate information, instruction, and training to employees to ensure their health and safety at work, as stated in the Health and Safety at Work etc. Act 1974. Induction training is a fundamental aspect of meeting these legal obligations.</p><h4 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-49_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-51_">Safe work practices</span></h4><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Safe_work_practices_through_induction_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690549016" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Safe_work_practices_through_induction_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690549016 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Safe_work_practices_through_induction_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690549016 320w" width="2000" height="1333" alt="Safe work practices through induction training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Safe work practices through induction training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:2000 / 1333" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-52_"/><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-53_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Induction training educates employees about safe work practices, procedures, and protocols. It covers manual handling techniques, infection control measures, proper personal protective equipment (PPE) use, and emergency procedures.</p><h4 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-55_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-57_">Risk management</span></h4><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Risk_management_achieved_in_induction_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690549252" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Risk_management_achieved_in_induction_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690549252 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Risk_management_achieved_in_induction_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690549252 320w" width="1797" height="1208" alt="Risk management achieved in induction training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Risk management achieved in induction training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:1797 / 1208" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-58_"/><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-59_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">When employees understand the risks related to their job duties, they can more easily recognise potential hazards and inform their supervisors or management. Taking this proactive approach helps with managing risks effectively within the organisation.<br><br>A well-organised induction program can decrease the chances of workplace incidents and accidents, resulting in fewer injuries and illnesses for employees and service users.</p><h4 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-61_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-63_">Creating a positive safety culture</span></h4><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Creating_a_positive_safety_culture_though_induction_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690549656" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Creating_a_positive_safety_culture_though_induction_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690549656 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Creating_a_positive_safety_culture_though_induction_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690549656 320w" width="2339" height="1453" alt="Creating a positive safety culture though induction training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Creating a positive safety culture though induction training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:2339 / 1453" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-64_"/><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-65_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Induction training sets the tone for a positive safety culture within the organisation. When new employees experience a strong emphasis on health and safety from the beginning, they are more likely to adopt safe practices throughout their employment.<br><br>Adequately trained employees feel more self-assured while performing their duties, particularly when working with vulnerable individuals in the health and social care industry. This confidence enables them to provide superior quality care and assistance to the service users.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-67_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-69_">Empower your team: Manage induction training as a trainer</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empower_your_team_Manage_induction_training_as_a_trainer-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690550130" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empower_your_team_Manage_induction_training_as_a_trainer-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1690550130 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empower_your_team_Manage_induction_training_as_a_trainer-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1690550130 320w" width="2162" height="1456" alt="Empower your team Manage induction training as a trainer- The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Empower your team Manage induction training as a trainer- The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:2162 / 1456" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-70_"/><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-71_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" da